BOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]]:'''\n** '''Winners (7):''' 1968, 1971, 1976, 1984, 1987, 1996, 2000\n** Runners-up (2): 1964, 2020\n** Third place (2): 1960, 2004\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Association football|Brazil}}\n* [[Brasil Global Tour]]\n* [[Brazil national football team results (2010\u201319)]]\n* [[Brazil national under-23 football team]]\n* [[Brazil national under-20 football team]]\n* [[Brazil national under-17 football team]]\n* [[Brazil national futsal team]]\n* [[Argentina\u2013Brazil football rivalry]]\n* [[Brazilian football songs]]\n* [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]]\n* [[List of Brazil national football team managers]]\n\n==References==\n\n'''Notes'''\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n'''Citations'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{cite book | author=Ruy Castro, Andrew Downie (translator) | title=Garrincha \u2013 The triumph and tragedy of Brazil's forgotten footballing hero | publisher=Yellow Jersey Press, London| year=2005| isbn=0-224-06433-9}}\n* {{cite book | author=Ivan Soter | title=Enciclop\u00e9dia da Sele\u00e7\u00e3o:100 anos de sele\u00e7\u00e3o brasileira de futebol | publisher=Folha Seca, Rio de Janeiro | year=2015| isbn=978-85-87199-29-4}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Brazil national association football team}}\n* [http://www.cbf.com.br/ Confedera\u00e7ao Brasilera de Futbol] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.fifa.com/associations/association=bra/index.html Brazil FIFA profile]\n* [http://www.brazilian-football.com/ Brazilian Football \u2013 Guide to Football in Brazil]\n* [http://www.rsssfbrasil.com/ RSSSF Brazil]\n* [http://www.sambafoot.com All about Brazilian Football \u2013 Sambafoot.com]\n\n{{Brazil national football team}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Link to related articles\n| titlestyle = background:#FFDF00; color:#009111; border:1px solid blue;\n| list1 =\n{{Brazil national football team records}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Brazil national football team \u2013 Achievements and Awards\n| titlestyle = background:#FFDF00; colo