{"title_page": "Vladimir Voskoboinikov", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Vladimir Voskoboinikov\n| image          = V-Voskoboinikov.jpg\n| fullname       = Vladimir Voskoboinikov\n| height         = {{height|m=1.88}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|02|02}}\n| birth_place    = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)#Centre forward|Centre forward]]\n| youthyears1 = 1991\u20132001\n| youthclubs1 = [[FC Puuma Tallinn|Puuma]]\n| years1 = 2001\u20132004 | caps1 = 80 | goals1 = 25 | clubs1 = [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]\n| years2 = 2004\u20132006 | caps2 =  8 | goals2 =  0 | clubs2 = [[FC Brussels|Brussels]]\n| years3 = 2005      | caps3 =  8 | goals3 =  1 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]] (loan)\n| years4 = 2006      | caps4 =  8 | goals4 =  4 | clubs4 = [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]\n| years5 = 2007\u20132008 | caps5 = 50 | goals5 = 12 | clubs5 = [[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]]\n| years6 = 2009      | caps6 = 17 | goals6 =  2 | clubs6 = [[Syrianska FC|Syrianska]]\n| years7 = 2009      | caps7 =  8 | goals7 =  0 | clubs7 = [[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch-Energiya Vladivostok]]\n| years8 = 2010      | caps8 =  9 | goals8 =  1 | clubs8 = [[Neftchi Baku PFC|Neftchi Baku]]\n| years9 = 2010\u20132011 | caps9 =  0 | goals9 =  0 | clubs9 = [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]\n| years10= 2011\u20132012 | caps10= 39 | goals10=  4 | clubs10= [[FC Khimki|Khimki]]\n| years11= 2012      | caps11= 13 | goals11=  1 | clubs11= [[FC Dinamo Tbilisi|Dinamo Tbilisi]]\n| years12= 2013\u20132015 | caps12= 43 | goals12= 28 | clubs12= [[N\u00f5mme Kalju FC|N\u00f5mme Kalju]]\n| years13= 2014      | caps13= 28 | goals13=  5 | clubs13= \u2192 [[Qingdao Hainiu F.C.|Qingdao Hainiu]] (loan)\n| years14= 2016\u20132017     | caps14= 59  | goals14= 20  | clubs14= [[FC Infonet|Infonet]]\n| pcupdate       = 18 November 2017\n| nationalyears1 = 2000      | nationalcaps1  =  1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalteam1  = [[Estonia national under-19 football team|Estonia U19]]\n| nationalyears2 = 2001\u20132003 | nationalcaps2  =  9 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalteam2  = [[Estonia national under-21 football team|Estonia U21]]\n| nationalyears3 = 2007\u20132013| nationalcaps3  = 36 | nationalgoals3 = 4 | nationalteam3  = [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]]\n|manageryears1  = |managerclubs1  = \n}}\n'''Vladimir Voskoboinikov''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0412\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432}}; born 2 February 1983) is a retired [[Estonia]]n professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre forward|centre forward]].\n\n==Club career==\nVoskoboinikov has begun his career at [[FC Puuma Tallinn|Puuma]] in Estonia where he played since 1991 until 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fcpuuma.ee/eng/history/|title=Football club Puma - the history|website=www.fcpuuma.ee}}</ref>\n\nAt the age of 18, Voskoboinikov continued his professional career with [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]. He has had a short spell in Belgium with [[Belgian First Division A|Jupiler League]] club [[FC Brussels|Brussels]] and a short loan at [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]] before he moved back to Estonia.\n\nHe was initially on loan at [[Russian First Division]] club [[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]], but in July 2007 he signed a two-year contract.\n\nOn 27 March 2009 he joined Swedish [[Superettan]] side [[Syrianska FC|Syrianska]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.postimees.ee/99939/voskoboinikov-siirdus-rootsi-esiliigasse|title=Voskoboinikov siirdus Rootsi esiliigasse|date=27 March 2009|website=[[Postimees]]}}</ref> Although he still had a running contract with FC Torpedo, he was given a free transfer, due to the rule that does not allow any foreign players in [[Russian Second Division]].\n\nIn January 2010 he joined [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] club [[Neftchi Baku PFC|Neftchi Baku]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccernet.ee/artikkel/voskoboinikovist-sai-jarjekordne-koondislane-neftsis|title=Voskoboinikovist sai j\u00e4rjekordne koondislane Neft\u0161is|first=Siim|last=Pulst|date=29 January 2010|website=Soccernet.ee}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2010, he joined Levadia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.postimees.ee/296967/voskoboinikov-liitus-levadiaga|title=Voskoboinikov liitus Levadiaga|date=7 August 2010|website=[[Postimees]]}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2011, he joined [[FC Khimki|Khimki]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccernet.ee/artikkel/voskoboinikov-siirdus-himkisse|title=Voskoboinikov siirdus Himkisse|first=Kristjan|last=Remmelkoor|date=10 February 2011|website=Soccernet.ee}}</ref>\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"50\" rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!width=\"50\" rowspan=\"2\"|League level\n!width=\"120\" rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Reserves\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n|-\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n|-\n|2001||rowspan=4|[[Meistriliiga|1]]||rowspan=4|[[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]||0||0||27||6||||||||\n|-\n|2002||0||0||14||5||||||||\n|-\n|2003||4||0||17||5||||||||\n|-\n|2004||18||9||0||0||||||||\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2004\u201305||[[Belgian First Division|1]]||[[FC Brussels|Brussels]]||8||0||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|[[Belgian Second Division|2]]||[[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]]||8||1||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|2005\u201306||[[Belgian First Division|1]]||[[FC Brussels|Brussels]]||0||0||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|2006||[[Meistriliiga|1]]||[[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]||8||4||||||||||||\n|-\n|2007||rowspan=2|[[Russian First Division|2]]||rowspan=2|[[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo]]||26||9||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|2008||24||3||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009||[[Superettan|2]]||[[Syrianska FC|Syrianska]]||17||2||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|[[Russian First Division|2]]||[[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch-Energiya]]||8||0||||||||||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|2009\u201310||[[Azerbaijan Premier League|1]]||[[Neftchi Baku PFC|Neftchi Baku]]||9||1||||||2||0||\u2014||\u2014\n|-\n|2010||rowspan=2|[[Meistriliiga|1]]||rowspan=2|[[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]||0||0||0||0||||||||\n|-\n|2011||0||0||0||0||||||||\n|-\n|2011||rowspan=2|[[Russian National Football League|2]]||rowspan=2|[[FC Khimki|Khimki]]||30||4||||||2||1||||\n|-\n|2012||9||0||||||||||||\n|-\n|2012\u201313||rowspan=1|[[Georgian Premier League|1]]||rowspan=1|[[FC Dinamo Tbilisi|Dinamo Tbilisi]]||13||1||||||2||5||||\n|-\n|2013||rowspan=1|[[Meistriliiga|1]]||rowspan=1|[[JK N\u00f5mme Kalju|Kalju]]||31||23||||||1||3||||\n|-\n|2014||rowspan=1|2||rowspan=1|[[Qingdao Hainiu F.C.|Qingdao Hainiu]]||28||5||||||3||1||||\n|-\n!colspan=11|''{{as of|2014|11|11}}.''\n|}\n\n==International career==\nFor [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]], Voskoboinikov is [[cap (sport)|capped]] 36 times, scoring 4 goals. He made his national team debut on 2 June 2007 against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2008 qualification]]. He scored his first national team goal on 18 November 2008, in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]] in a Mayors Cup match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccernet.ee/artikkel/vosko-esimene-varav-toi-moldova-ule-voidu|title=Vosko esimene v\u00e4rav t\u00f5i Moldova \u00fcle v\u00f5idu|date=18 November 2008|website=Soccernet.ee}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jalgpall.ee/news.php?st=style_fp.css&news_id=726|title=K\u00f5ik Eesti internatsionaalid|publisher=[[Eesti Jalgpalli Liit]]|accessdate=9 May 2013|language=Estonian|trans-title=All Estonian internationals}}</ref>\n\n===International goals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competi