re forward|centre forward]].\n\n==Club career==\nVoskoboinikov has begun his career at [[FC Puuma Tallinn|Puuma]] in Estonia where he played since 1991 until 2000.<ref>[http://www.fcpuuma.ee/eng/history/ Voskoboinikov, the beginning \u2013 fcpuuma.ee]</ref>\n\nAt the age of 18, Voskoboinikov continued his professional career with [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia]]. He has had a short spell in Belgium with [[Belgian First Division A|Jupiler League]] club [[FC Brussels|Brussels]] and a short loan at [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]] before he moved back to Estonia.\n\nHe was initially on loan at [[Russian First Division]] club [[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]], but in July 2007 he signed a two-year contract.\n\nOn 27 March 2009 he joined Swedish [[Superettan]] side [[Syrianska FC|Syrianska]].<ref>[http://sport.postimees.ee/?id=99939 Voskoboinikov siirdus Rootsi esiliigasse \u2013 Postimees.ee] {{in lang|et}}</ref> Although he still had a running contract with FC Torpedo, he was given a free transfer, due to the rule that does not allow any foreign players in [[Russian Second Division]].\n\nIn January 2010 he joined [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] club [[Neftchi Baku PFC|Neftchi Baku]].<ref>[http://www.soccernet.ee/voskoboinikovist-sai-jarjekordne-koondislane-neftsis Voskoboinikovist sai j\u00e4rjekordne koondislane Neft\u0161is] {{in lang|et}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2010, he joined Levadia.<ref>http://sport.postimees.ee/?id=296967</ref>\n\nIn February 2011, he joined [[FC Khimki|Khimki]].<ref>http://www.soccernet.ee/voskoboinikov-siirdus-himkisse</ref>\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"50\" rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!width=\"50\" rowspan=\"2\"|League level\n!width=\"120\" rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Reserves\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n|-\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|Games\n!width=\"50\"|Goals\n!width=\"50\"|