atia]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2008 qualification]]. He scored his first national team goal on 18 November 2008, in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]] in a Mayors Cup match.<ref>[http://www.soccernet.ee/news.php?id=22639 Vosko t\u00f5i Moldova \u00fcle v\u00f5idu \u2013 Soccernet.ee] {{in lang|et}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jalgpall.ee/news.php?st=style_fp.css&news_id=726|title=K\u00f5ik Eesti internatsionaalid|publisher=[[Eesti Jalgpalli Liit]]|accessdate=9 May 2013|language=Estonian|trans-title=All Estonian internationals}}</ref>\n\n===International goals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-align=center\n|1\n|align=left|18 November 2008\n|align=left|[[Lillek\u00fcla Stadium]], [[Tallinn]], Estonia\n|align=left|{{fb|MDA}}\n|1\u20130\n|1\u20130\n|align=left|Mayors Cup\n|-align=center\n|2\n|align=left|6 June 2009\n|align=left|[[Lillek\u00fcla Stadium]], [[Tallinn]], Estonia\n|align=left|{{fb|EQG}}\n|2\u20130\n|3\u20130\n|align=left|[[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-align=center\n|3\n|align=left|5 September 2009\n|align=left|[[Kadir Has Stadium]], [[Kayseri]], Turkey\n|align=left|{{fb|TUR}}\n|1\u20130\n|2\u20134\n|align=left|[[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-align=center\n|4\n|align=left|3 June 2012\n|align=left|[[Tamme Stadium]], [[Tartu]], Estonia\n|align=left|{{fb|LIT}}\n|1\u20130\n|1\u20130\n|align=left|[[2012 Baltic Cup]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"12\"|<small>''Correct as of 13 January 2017''<ref>[https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=22386 Football PLAYER: Vladimir Voskoboinikov]</ref></small>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;Levadia\n* [[Meistriliiga]]: [[2004 Meistriliiga|2004]], [[2006 Meistriliiga|2006]]\n* [[Estonian Cup]]: [[2001\u201302 Estonian Cup|2001\u201302]], [[2003\u201304 Estonian Cup|2003\u201304]]\n\n;Brussels\n* [[Belgian Second Division]]: 2003\u201304\n\n;N\u00f5mme Kalju\n* [[Estonian Cup]]: [[2014